e complete picture of a threat actor. We describe some of these overlapping features below.\\n\\nSource: https://securelist.com/blog/incidents/73914/operation-blockbuster-revealed/\", \"created\": \"2016-02-25T15:08:29.112000\", \"modified\": \"2016-02-25T15:08:29.112000\", \"references\": [\"https://securelist.com/blog/incidents/73914/operation-blockbuster-revealed/\", \"https://www.operationblockbuster.com/resources/index.html\", \"http://www.kaspersky.com/about/news/virus/2016/Kaspersky-Lab-helps-to-disrupt-activity-of-Lazarus-Group-responsible-for-multiple-devastating-cyber-attacks\"], \"indicators\": [], \"indicator_count\": 0}, {\"pulse_id\": \"56d09e59aef921516b81fba1\", \"indicator\": \"Lazarus Group\", \"type\": \"pulse\", \"pulse_name\": \"Operation Blockbuster: The Lazarus Group\", \"tags\": [\"threat connect\", \"advanced persistent threat\", \"apt\", \"lazarus group\", \"operation blockbuster\", \"sony\"], \"first_seen\": \"2016-02-26T18:50:01.589000\", \"last_seen\": \"2016-02-26T18:50:01.589000\", \"adversary\": null, \"malware_families\": [], \"targeted_countries\": [], \"name\": \"Operation Blockbuster: The Lazarus Group\", \"description\": \"Operation Blockbuster is a Novetta led coalition that analyzed the Advanced Persistent Threat adversary responsible for the devastating and destructive attack against Sony Pictures in 2014. The threat has been dubbed the Lazarus Group , and is tied to use of specific similar malicious code variants going back to 2009. The actor has been identified in attacks on government , Military , Media , Aerospace , Finance , and Critical Infrastructure victims, most of which are in the United States and South Korea . The scope of this group indicates that it is operated by a well-funded and resourced entity, not merely a hacktivist group.\", \"created\": \"2016-02-26T18:50:01.589000\", \"modified\": \"2016-02-26T18:50:01.589000\", \"references\": [\"https://app.threatconnect.com/auth/threat/threat.xhtml?threat=988382\"], 